tificate training? - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Who should undertake care certificate training? - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-leSONj uTJGF pf-15_"/></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-a995" data-category="Generic Content" data-name="Matcha" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-jefHZX ePVSNw pf-16_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-ihINtW iHyUfe"><div class="sc-iAKWXU lesjfG pf-17_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:0px;--s-sm:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-bXdNzS hYBROi pf-18_"><p class="sc-dYtuZ JoqQF pf-19_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eTwdGJ utmwk pf-21_">The Care Certificate is an indispensable training program designed for individuals entering specific roles within healthcare and adult social care sectors. It equips new workers with the fundamental skills, knowledge, values, and behaviours required to provide exceptional care. While the certification primarily targets new professionals, it also holds great potential for existing workers looking to advance their careers as in-house trainers. In this blog, we will discuss who can benefit from <a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/products/care-certificate-train-the-trainer-trainer-pack-cpduk-accredited?variant=31839814582341" target="_blank"><i><span style="color: rgb(0, 102, 204);">Care Certificate</span></i></a> training and the advantages of completing it.</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-jeraig eTNnJl pf-22_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eTwdGJ utmwk pf-24_">The Care Certificate: A foundation for success</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Understanding_the_Care_Certificate_curriculum_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1692875088" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Understanding_the_Care_Certificate_curriculum_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1692875088 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Understanding_the_Care_Certificate_curriculum_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1692875088 320w" width="1888" height="1258" alt="The Care Certificate: A foundation for success - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="The Care Certificate: A foundation for success - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-leSONj uTJGF pf-25_"/><p class="sc-dYtuZ JoqQF pf-26_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eTwdGJ utmwk pf-28_">The Care Certificate encompasses a comprehensive training curriculum that covers fifteen standards, ranging from understanding your role to infection prevention and control. It is considered the top standard for training new healthcare and adult social care workers in specific positions, providing them with the skills and knowledge they need to provide safe, effective, compassionate, and high-quality care. </span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-jeraig eTNnJl pf-29_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eTwdGJ utmwk pf-31_">Candidates for the Care Certificate </span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Essential_skills_for_healthcare_professionals_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1692875188" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Essential_skills_for_healthcare_professionals_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1692875188 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Essential_skills_for_healthcare_professionals_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1692875188 320w" width="1787" height="1191" alt="Candidates for the Care Certificate - train the trainer - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Candidates for the Care Certificate - train the trainer - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-leSONj uTJGF pf-32_"/><p class="sc-dYtuZ JoqQF pf-33_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-eTwdGJ utmwk pf-35_">The Care Certificate is tailored to individuals joining health or adult social care organisations without previous training or experience in the sector. It caters to a wide range of roles within the healthcare and adult social care settings, including: </span></p><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-emDsmM BOtMC pf-36_">Healthcare</h3><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-aaqME bBWRSi pf-38_"><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-iRFsWr jqRXMU pf-39_">Healthcare Support Workers</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-iRFsWr jqRXMU pf-41_">Health Care Assistants</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-iRFsWr jqRXMU pf-43_">Assistant Practitioners</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-iRFsWr jqRXMU pf-45_">Individuals supporting clinical roles in the NHS involving direct patient contact.</li></ul><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-emDsmM BOtMC pf-47_">Adult Social Care</h3><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-aaqME bBWRSi pf-49_"><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-iRFsWr jqRXMU pf-50_">Care Assistants</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-iRFsWr jqRXMU pf-52_">Care Workers</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-iRFsWr jqRXMU pf-54_">Homecare Workers</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-iRFsWr jqRXMU pf-56_">Care Support Workers</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-iRFsWr jqRXMU pf-58_">Professionals providing direct care in various settings like residential homes, nursing homes, hospices, domiciliary care, supported living services etc.</li></ul><p